{{Quote|We have stolen a small Imperial shuttle. Disguised as a cargo ship, and using a secret Imperial code, a strike team will land on the moon and deactivate the shield generator.|General Crix Madine|audio=Madine-Imperialshuttlestolen.flac|<ref name="ROTJ" />}}
'''Crix Madine''' was a [[human]] [[Gender|male]] who led a [[Imperial commando|commando]] unit of the [[Galactic Empire]]'s [[Imperial Military|military]] until he defected to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]], where he served as a [[general]]. As the [[officer]] responsible for covert actions, he devised the [[Battle of Endor|attack]] on the [[Endor]] [[Deflector shield|shield]] [[Deflector shield generator|generator]] and trained the [[Rebel trooper|soldiers]] who accompanied [[Han Solo]] to the forest [[moon]]. At the end of the [[Galactic Civil War]], Madine went on to serve in the [[New Republic]], a [[Democracy|democratic]] [[Politics|government]] [[Declaration of a New Republic|founded]] by the Alliance.

==Biography==
===Early life===
[[File:Imperial_Madine.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Crix Madine in his Imperial days]]
A [[human]] [[Gender|male]] [[Homeworld|native]] to [[Corellia]]<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> [[Reproduction|born]] in [[34 BBY]],<ref name="Scum" /> Crix Madine initially served in the [[Imperial Military|military]] of the [[Galactic Empire]], an authoritarian regime [[Proclamation of the New Order|founded]] at the end of the [[Clone Wars]], in which he led a [[Imperial commando|commando]] unit.<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> He became a highly decorated officer,<ref name="RotJ novel">[[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (paperback novel)|''Star Wars: Return of the Jedi'' junior novelization]]</ref> and obtained the [[military rank]] of [[general]].<ref name="Lead by Example">''[[Lead by Example]]''</ref> However, he ended up defecting to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]], a resistance group that opposed the tyranny of the Empire during the [[Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> Holding the rank of [[General]], he specialized in covert actions that involved the theft of equipment from the Empire and infiltration of strike teams onto occupied [[Planet|worlds]].<ref name="SWE">{{SWE|characters|general-madine|General Madine}}</ref> He was a practitioner of [[Corellian boxing]].<ref name="TFA head to head" />

===Galactic Civil War===
====Aboard ''Home One''====
Madine was present on ''[[Home One]]'' alongside [[Chancellor (Rebel Alliance)|Chancellor]] [[Mon Mothma]] and [[Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar|Ackbar]] when [[bounty hunter]] [[Beilert Valance]] provided the Rebellion with the plans for a [[Deflector shield generator|shield generator]] that could withstand [[orbital bombardment]].<ref name="Empire Ascendant 1">{{StoryCite|story=Two Sides to Every Sortie|book=Empire Ascendant 1}}</ref>

====Operation Yellow Moon====
[[File:Death_Star_II_revealed.png|thumb|right|250px|Madine and several other members of the Alliance's leadership discuss the Death Star II.]]
Several [[Standard month|months]] after the [[Battle of Hoth|battle]] of [[Hoth]], Madine and other [[Alliance High Command|high-ranking rebel officers]] secretly met on [[Zastiga]], where Chancellor Mothma revealed that the Alliance had discovered the Empire was building a new planet-killing [[battle station]], the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|second Death Star]], over the [[Forest]] [[Moon]] of [[Endor]]. The Alliance decided to destroy the battle station before it was completed, but needed time to gather the [[Rebel Alliance Navy|Alliance Fleet]] near [[Sullust]]. [[Princess]] [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]] proposed leading a mission, dubbed [[Operation Yellow Moon]], to distract the Empire's attention to the [[Corva sector]] on the opposite side of [[the galaxy]] from Sullust.<ref name="Moving Target">''[[Moving Target: A Princess Leia Adventure]]''</ref>

Madine and the other rebel [[commander]]s agreed with her plan, and Madine volunteered to serve on the mission as a [[Rebel Commando|commando]]. Admiral Ackbar rejected him, noting that he was needed to plan the assault on the second Death Star. Instead, Madine assigned one of his best [[commando]]s, [[Major]] [[Lokmarcha]], to the mission. Leia succeeded in completing the operation, although Lokmarcha and [[Antrot|another]] rebel operative died. Leia also managed to steal the ''[[Tydirium]]'', an Imperial [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]], which Madine intended to use on the mission to Endor.<ref name="Moving Target" />

====Battle of Endor====
{{Quote|General Solo, is your strike team assembled?|General Madine, to his colleague Han Solo|<ref name="ROTJ" />}}
[[File:Madine_Endor_Briefing.png|thumb|left|300px|Madine briefs the Alliance forces on the ground assault part of the mission.]]
With the Alliance Fleet in place, Madine, Mothma, and Ackbar briefed Alliance forces on the plan to destroy the second Death Star.<ref name="ROTJ" /> Thanks to Leia's theft of the ''Tydirium'',<ref name="Moving Target" /> the general planned on sneaking a [[Special Forces Trackers Unit|strike team]] onto the Forest Moon of Endor, where the Empire had built a [[Deflector shield|shield]] [[Deflector shield generator|generator]] to protect the battle station. From the moon's surface, the Rebels could take down the shield generator, leaving the Death Star vulnerable to the Alliance Fleet's firepower. In order to accomplish that mission, Madine asked his fellow general [[Han Solo]] to assemble and lead the strike team.<ref name="ROTJ" />

Prior to the [[Battle of Endor]], General Madine gave a [[hologram]] briefing to the various starfighter squadrons in the Alliance Fleet including [[Corona Squadron]], which was based aboard the [[MC80 Star Cruiser|Mon Calamari cruiser]] ''[[Liberty]]''. When [[Kendy Idele]] asked who would take care of the deflector shield generator on Endor, Madine reassured her that Solo's team would handle that matter. When several Corona pilots including [[Yendor Brethen|Yendor]] chatted about Han, Madine interjected that Solo was one of their best assets. He then assigned Corona Squadron to escort General [[Landonis Balthazar Calrissian|Lando Calrissian]] in the ''[[Millennium Falcon]]'' and the [[Gold Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Gold]], [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Red]], [[Green Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Green]], and [[Gray Squadron (Rebel Alliance)|Gray Squadrons]] as they penetrated the second Death Star.<ref name="Lost Stars">''[[Lost Stars]]''</ref> Madine's plan ultimately succeeded, which led to the Alliance's most crucial victory over the Empire.<ref name="ROTJ" />

Following the destruction of the second Death Star, Madine kept the fleet on alert over the moon of Endor as he was concerned about a possible Imperial counterattack. The next day, Madine conferred with General Solo about an [[Imperial outpost (Endor)|Imperial outpost]] still operating on the other side of the moon from the shield generator. Both agreed that they could not allow the Imperials to remain and threaten the [[Ewok]]s, and Solo led his strike team in a [[Assault on an Imperial outpost|assault]] on the outpost.<ref name="SE1">[[Shattered Empire 1|''Shattered Empire'' 1]]</ref>

====War continues====
[[File:GeneralMadine-BaseSeries4.png|thumb|right|250px|General Madine continued efforts against the Empire after Endor.]]
{{Quote|&hellip;as much as Admiral Ackbar and I wish we could tell you the end is at hand, we see no respite from hostilities at this time&hellip;|General Madine, briefing rebel pilots and soldiers about Operation: Cinder|<ref name="SE4">[[Shattered Empire 4|''Shattered Empire'' 4]]</ref>}}
A few months after Endor, Madine and other elements of the Rebel Fleet Command were aboard a MC80 [[Star Cruiser]] at Muster Point: Stalwart. He and Admiral Gial Ackbar briefed rebel [[soldier]]s and [[pilot]]s on the Empire's ongoing planetary assaults, including [[Operation: Cinder]]. Madine thanked the rebels for their efforts against the Empire and for the thousands of lives they saved countering Operation: Cinder, but sadly noted that the war was far from over.<ref name="SE4" />

====New Republic service====
{{Quote|&hellip;This is a fragile peace. And we must be wary of any ruse set before us. General Madine, do you think you could put together a strike team? Small five to seven Republic soldiers.''"<br />"''I think that's doable. You want them on the ground?|Ackbar and Madine discussing the events on Akiva|<ref name="Aftermath" />}}
Sometime after the Battle of Endor, the Rebel Alliance was reorganized into the [[New Republic]] and Madine was placed in command of the [[New Republic Special Forces]]. After Admiral Ackbar received vital intelligence on Imperial fleet movements from a mysterious informant called [[Gallius Rax|the Operator]], General Madine was part of a hologram conference that included Commander [[Kyrsta Agate]], [[Captain]] [[Saff Melor]], and [[Chancellor (New Republic)|Chancellor]] Mon Mothma. When Madine questioned the trustworthiness of this informant, Agate responded that the Operator had been reliable so far. However, Ackbar cautioned that the Empire was playing a long game. At the advice of Ackbar, Madine agreed to divert a small team of Special Forces soldiers led by [[Sergeant]] [[Jom Barell]] to investigate the Imperial presence on [[Akiva]]. While most of the unit was killed, Barell played a role in the successful [[rebellion on Akiva]].<ref name="Aftermath" />

In [[5 ABY]],<ref name="Life Debt Date" /> Madine attended the [[Liberation Day (New Republic)|Liberation Day]] celebrations held at [[Chandrila]]'s [[Old Gather-House]]. Mothma had organized Liberation Day to celebrate the liberation of a hundred former rebel prisoners from [[Ashmead's Lock]] on the planet [[Kashyyyk]]. However, the prisoners had been fitted with inorganic biochip implants which allowed [[Fleet Admiral]] Gallius Rax, the true leader of the Imperial remnants, to transmit signals which turned the prisoners into unwilling assassins. Madine was rumored to have died during the [[attack on Chandrila]],<ref name="Life Debt" /> rumors that were neither confirmed nor denied by the New Republic even [[Standard decade|decades]] later.<ref name="Rise and Fall">''[[Star Wars: The Rise and Fall of the Galactic Empire]]''</ref>

==Personality and traits==
Crix Madine was a [[Color|blue]]-[[eye]]d man<ref name="ROTJ" /> of average height, standing 1.7 [[meter]]s.<ref name="Character Encyclopedia" /> He had reddish blond [[hair]] and, at the time of the Battle of Endor, he sported a full beard.<ref name="ROTJ" /> As an [[officer]], he was very respectful of the [[Rebel trooper|troopers]] under his command. He always made sure that his men were properly equipped and prepared for the dangerous missions he assigned to them.<ref name="SWE" /> While writing letters of notification to the loved ones of rebels who died in the line of duty, Madine used a protocol droid to assist him.<ref name="SE2">[[Shattered Empire 2|''Shattered Empire'' 2]]</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Madine_btm.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Unused shot of General Madine from ''Return of the Jedi''.]]
Crix Madine first appeared in the [[1983]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], the third and final installment of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[original trilogy]]. He was played by the [[Wikipedia:Ireland|Irish]] actor [[Dermot Crowley]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

When Crowley first walked onto the set he was smooth-faced and the crew presented him with a false beard insisting that he had to wear it. The [[Kenner Products]] toy company had already begun pre-production on Madine's action figure, and, since that toy sported a beard, Crowley had to match.<ref name="MakeROTJ">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref>

Given the uncertainty inherent in giving key expository dialog to the [[Mon Calamari]] Admiral Ackbar&mdash;portrayed by a fishfaced puppet&mdash;the filmmakers of ''Return of the Jedi'' shot a number of "backup" shots of Madine standing in for his colleague. However, those shots ultimately went unused in the movie's final cut.<ref name="MadineDB">{{DB|character|generalcrixmadine|Madine, General Crix}}</ref>

[[Dark Droids 1|''Dark Droids'' 1]] has Crix Madine already aware of the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|Death Star II]].<ref name="DD 1">[[Dark Droids 1|''Dark Droids'' 1]]</ref> However ''[[Moving Target: A Princess Leia Adventure]]'', in which Madine is informed of the Death Star II, takes place after ''Dark Droids''.<ref name="Moving Target" />

